xtensive%20that%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fmedicane-left-libya-trapped-between-floods-and-the-sea%2Fa-66793714%5C%22%3Ethe%20city%20was%20almost%20inaccessible%20to%20aid%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDerna%20lies%20on%20a%20narrow%20coastal%20plain%20on%20the%20Mediterranean%20under%20steep%20mountains.%20Only%20two%20roads%20from%20the%20south%20remain%20usable%2C%20hampering%20the%20movement%20of%20aid%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAid%20workers%20and%20officials%20have%20said%20that%20the%20death%20toll%20is%20likely%20to%20keep%20rising%2C%20as%20bodies%20continue%20to%20wash%20up%20ashore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBodies%20are%20everywhere%2C%20inside%20houses%2C%20in%20the%20streets%2C%20at%20sea.%20Wherever%20you%20go%2C%20you%20find%20dead%20men%2C%20women%2C%20and%20children%2C%E2%80%9D%20Emad%20al-Falah%2C%20an%20aid%20worker%20from%20Benghazi%2C%20told%20AP.%20%E2%80%9CEntire%20families%20were%20lost.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWar%20and%20corruption%20exacerbate%20disaster%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Libyan%20political%20analyst%20has%20called%20for%20the%20first%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Flibyans-increasingly-frustrated-with-politics-rising-prices-foreign-interference%2Fa-62402038%5C%22%3Egeneral%20elections%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20be%20held%20in%20almost%2010%20years%20after%20the%20internationally-recognised%20Government%20of%20National%20Unity%20(GNU)%20postponed%20accepting%20international%20aid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTwo%20rival%20governments%20that%20are%20perfectly%20happy%20to%20rule%20over%20the%20rubble%20whilst%20their%20citizens%20lay%20underneath%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%C2%A0Anas%20El%20Gomati%2C%20founder%20of%20Tripoli-based%C2%A0Sadeq%20Institute%2C%20told%20DW.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20the%20Red%20Crescent%20and%20Libyan%20civilians%20themselves%20have%20been%20responsible%20for%20the%20bulk%20of%20the%20disaster%20recovery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAnd%20frankly%