%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20as%20a%20Centre%20for%20New%20Economics%20Studies%20initiative%2C%20is%20based%20on%20exploring%20the%20intersectionality%20of%20gender%20across%20the%20discourse%20of%20development%20studies%2C%20social%20policy%2C%20and%20entrepreneurship.%20The%20team%20engage%20with%20narratives%20of%20individuals%20who%20are%20bridging%20gaps%20in%20societal%20expectations%20of%20gendered%20identities%2C%20highlighting%20their%20value%20creation%20process%2C%20as%20an%20expression%20of%20their%20creativity%2C%20with%20an%20objective%20to%20highlight%20hitherto%20under-represented%20voices%20in%20the%20mainstream%20discourse.%20Click%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fswaabhimaancnes.in%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ehere%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20to%20review%20its%20work.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHelplines%2C%20established%20through%20different%20state%20initiatives%2C%20have%20through%20the%20years%20expanded%20their%20reach%20to%20implement%20a%20speedy%20assistance%20mechanism%20for%20swift%20emergency%20redressal.%20They%20play%20a%20diverse%20role%20in%20assisting%20women%20and%20gendered%20minorities%20through%20the%20provision%20of%20counselling%2C%20emotional%20assistance%2C%20information%2C%20guidance%20and%20referrals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20in%20a%20nation%20packed%20with%20a%20rich%20kaleidoscopic%20base%20of%20cultural%20and%20ethnic%20diversity%2C%20establishing%20an%20efficient%20helpline%20tests%20the%20skills%20and%20policy%20frameworks%20designed%20by%20the%20state.%20What%20one%20often%20finds%20is%20a%20large%20volume%20or%20stack%20of%20data%20in%20files%20at%20the%20office%20of%20a%20ministry%2C%20holding%20the%20hopes%20of%20those%20looking%20for%20emergency%20assistance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHelplines%2C%20while%20designed%20as%20an%20emergency-based%20redressal%20mechanism%2C%20may%20subsequently%20remain%20even%20less%20accessible%20to%20those%20who%20need%20it%20the%20most.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20with%20other%20public%20emergencies%20and%20disasters%2C%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20has%20contributed%20to%20an%20increase%20in%20gender-based%20violence.%20Domestic%20violence%20had%20significantly%20increased%20worldwide%20as%20more%20women%20were%20being%20coerced%20into%20living%20with%20their%20offenders.%20Even%20though%20a%20disaster%20does%20not%20%E2%80%98select%E2%80%99%20who%20would%20be%20worst%20affected%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcompass.onlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2F10.1111%2Fsoc4.12080%5C%22%3Ecertain%20individuals%20are%20more%20vulnerable%20than%20others%3C%2Fa%3E%20due%20to%20the%20fragile%20socio-ecological%20systems%20and%20social%20stratification.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20during%20times%20of%20lockdown%2C%20the%20need%20for%20domestic%20violence%20helplines%20increased%20significantly%2C%20making%20them%20an%20increasingly%20important%20source%20of%20assistance%20for%20survivors.%20Virtual%20support%20offered%20by%20DA%20helplines%20(including%20call%2C%20text%2C%20webchat%20and%20email%20services)%20became%20an%20increasingly%20important%20avenue%20for%20victim%20support%20in%20the%20context%20of%20lockdown%20and%20the%20ensuing%20effects%20on%20the%20economy%2C%20the%20working%20environment%20and%20social%20arrangements%2C%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20access%20to%20previously%20available%20face-to-face%20or%20community-based%20support%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESystemic%20violations%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%2C%20there%20are%20currently%20more%20than%2052%20helplines%20active%20throughout%20the%20nation.%20To%20accept%20reports%20of%20domestic%20violence%20during%20the%20lockdown%2C%20the%20National%20Commission%20of%20Women%20(NCW)%20has%20started%20using%20the%20WhatsApp%20number%207217735372.%20This%20complements%20already-existing%20emails%2C%20online%20forms%20and%20communication%20via%20Facebook%20and%20Twitter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20helpline%20numbers%20accessible%20for%2024%2F7%20counselling%20services%2C%20rescue%20efforts%20and%20shelter%20homes.%20Many%20successful%20interventions%20have%20taken%20place%2C%20and%20thousands%20of%20women%20have%20used%20these%20services%20to%20ask%20for%20assistance.%20These%20procedures%2C%20however%2C%20might%20not%20be%20adequate%20given%20the%20obstacles%20to%20reporting%20that%20have%20led%20to%20blatant%20underreporting.%20Primary%20constraints%20include%20a%20lack%20of%20money%20and%20technology%2C%20as%20well%20as%20tight%20limitations%20on%20mobility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20lockdown%2C%20Oxfam%20India%E2%80%99s%20lead%20specialist%20for%20gender%20justice%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oxfamindia.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2020-07%2FOxfam%2520India%2520Submission%2520to%2520the%2520UNSR-VAWG.pdf%5C%22%3EAmita%20Pitre%20explained%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20organisation%E2%80%99s%20first%20action%20was%20to%20compile%20a%20list%20of%20all%20of%20the%20helplines%20and%20counsellors%E2%80%99%20contact%20information%20nationwide%20as%20well%20as%20the%20locations%20where%20Oxfam%20India%20operates.%20They%20then%20verified%20each%20entry%20twice%20to%20make%20sure%20it%20was%20operational.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20single%20national%20helpline%20number%2C%20Pitre%20talked%20about%20the%20challenges%20of%20promoting%20helplines%20and%20creating%20awareness.%20It%20becomes%20increasingly%20apparent%20that%20civil%20society%20organisations%20carried%20out%20micro-level%20awareness-raising%20for%20helplines%20as%20opposed%20to%20doing%20so%20through%20mainstream%20media%20campaigns%20on%20television%2C%20radio%20and%20newspapers%2C%20which%20had%20its%20own%20limitations%20in%20terms%20of%20resource%20constraints%20and%20bureaucratic%20censorship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20mental%20health%20crisis%20was%20another%20catastrophe%20that%20developed%20concurrently%20with%20domestic%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20disregarding%20hundreds%20of%20cases%2C%20the%20Modi%20government%20finally%20acknowledged%20the%20necessity%20for%20a%20reliable%2C%20round-the-clock%20helpline%20for%20suicide%20prevention%20and%20introduced%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia-news%2Fgovt-launches-24x7-toll-free-mental-rehabilitation-helpline-kiran-in-13-languages%2Fstory-JSfacmFtDqpmht2km9nzGK.html%5C%22%3EKIRAN%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20hotline%20for%20mental%20health%20rehabilitation%20that%20is%20available%20in%2013%20different%20languages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20more%20distressing%20is%20the%20fact%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindubusinessline.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fhuge-gap-in-indias-mental-health-budget%2Farticle30733494.ece%5C%22%3Eonly%20Rs%205%20crore%20of%20the%20allocated%20funds%20%3C%2Fa%3Ewere%20actually%20used%20in%20the%20fiscal%20years%202018%20and%202019%20%E2%80%93%20representing%20a%20reduction%20of%20Rs%2010%20crore%20from%20the%20prior%20year%E2%80%99s%20allocation%20of%20just%20Rs%2040%20crore%20for%20mental%20health.%20In%20order%20to%20put%20this%20into%20perspective%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC6482705%2F%5C%22%3Ea%20research%20published%20in%20the%20Indian%20Journal%20of%20Psychiatry%3C%2Fa%3E%20projected%20that%20it%20would%20cost%20Rs%2094%2C073%20crore%20to%20execute%20the%20Mental%20Healthcare%20Act%20of%202017.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20issue%20is%20related%20to%20the%20lack%20of%20internal%20capacity%20development%20among%20those%20answering%20calls%20from%20survivors.%20Most%20therapists%20were%20trained%20for%20in-person%20sessions%20rather%20than%20online%20counseling.%20Some%20therapists%20were%20obliged%20to%20urge%20women%20to%20visit%20them%20once%20the%20lockdown%20was%20over%20due%20to%20a%20lack%20of%20available%20services%3B%20more%20challenging%20problems%2C%20such%20as%20educating%20them%20about%20their%20rights%20and%20where%20to%20find%20resources%2C%20proved%20to%20be%20more%20challenging.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20since%20many%20of%20these%20organisations%20have%20a%20small%20staff%2C%20with%20only%20a%20couple%20of%20employees%20handling%20calls%20from%20across%20the%20nation.%20Most%20helplines%20also%20lack%20professional%20therapists.%20Young%2C%20college-bound%20volunteers%20and%20psychology%20students%20typically%20take%20on%20the%20task%20of%20running%20the%20helplines%20after%20completing%20a%20brief%20training%2C%20and%20they%20may%20lack%20experience%20and%20knowledge%20when%20dealing%20with%20customers%20in%20extremely%20traumatic%20situations.%20Employees%20with%20inadequate%20training%20may%20come%20out%20as%20condescending.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20lot%20needs%20to%20be%20still%20done%20in%20improving%20and%20decentralising%20emergency%20response%20infrastructure%20in%2Facross%20India.%20States%20also%20need%20support%20from%20the%20Centre%20for%20financing%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDeepanshu%20Mohan%20is%20Professor%20of%20Economics%20and%20Director%2C%20Centre%20for%20New%20Economics%20Studies%20(CNES)%2C%20Jindal%20School%20of%20Liberal%20Arts%20and%20Humanities%2C%20O.P.%20Jindal%20Global%20University.%20Tavleen%20Kaur%20is%20a%20Senior%20Research%20Assistant%20with%20CNES%20and%20the%20Team%20Lead%20for%20Swabhimaan.%20Anvitha%20Gowda%20is%20a%20Research%20Analyst%20with%20CNES%20and%20Team%20Co-Lead%20for%20Swabhimaan.%20Shalaka%20Adhikari%20and%20Archisha%20Tiwari%20are%20Research%20Analysts%20with%20CNES%20and%20members%20of%20team%20Swabhimaan%20and%20CIDS.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694598613000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fanalysing-emergency-response-a-basic-assessment-of-helplines-in-india%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20lot%20needs%20to%20be%20still%20done%20in%20improving%20and%20decentralising%20emergency%20response%20infrastructure%20in%2Facross%20India.%20States%20also%20need%20support%20from%20the%20Centre%20for%20financing%20needs.%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fanalysing-emergency-response-a-basic-assessment-of-helplines-in-india%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Byju%E2%80%99s%20'Transferred'%20%24533%20Million%20to%20a%20Hedge%20Fund%20That%20Houses%20US%20Pancake%20Shop%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F12%2F15190825%2Fimage-652.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ELast%20year%2C%20edtech%20firm%20Byju%E2%80%99s%20US%20subsidiary%2C%20Alpha%20Inc%2C%20allegedly%20transferred%20%24533%20million%20to%20Camshaft%20Capital%20Fund%2C%20an%20investment%20firm%20established%20three%20years%20ago%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2023-09-12%2Fbyju-s-hid-533-million-in-hedge-fund-camshaft-run-from-miami-ihop-lenders-say%23xj4y7vzkg%5C%22%3Ereports%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businesstoday.in%2Fentrepreneurship%2Fnews%2Fstory%2Fbyjus-lenders-using-bogus-loan-default-claims-to-gain-control-ed-tech-firm-tells-us-court-392938-2023-08-05%5C%22%3Eciting%20claims%3C%2Fa%3E%20made%20by%20some%20of%20Byju%E2%80%99s%20lenders%20in%20a%20lawsuit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2023-09-12%2Fbyju-s-hid-533-million-in-hedge-fund-camshaft-run-from-miami-ihop-lenders-say%23xj4y7vzkg%5C%22%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20this%20hedge%20fund%20was%20established%20by%20William%20C.%20Morton%2C%20at%20the%20age%20of%2023.%20And%20these%20lenders%20allege%20that%20Byju%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Chid%E2%80%9D%20the%20money%20in%20this%20hedge%20fund.%20They%20contend%20that%20Morton%E2%80%99s%20fund%20received%20this%20substantial%20amount%20despite%20his%20apparent%20lack%20of%20formal%20investment%20training.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20court%20documents%20reveal%20that%20luxury%20cars%2C%20including%20a%202023%20Ferrari%20Roma%2C%20a%202020%20Lamborghini%20Hurac%C3%A1n%20EVO%2C%20and%20a%202014%20Rolls-Royce%20Wraith%2C%20have%20been%20registered%20in%20Morton%E2%80%99s%20name%20since%20the%20transfer%20took%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20in%20a%202020%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Commission%20filing%2C%20Camshaft%20noted%20its%20main%20business%20address%20as%20285%20NW%2042nd%20Ave.%20This%20address%20actually%20houses%20an%20IHOP%20restaurant%20(a%20pancake%20shop)%20in%20Miami%E2%80%99s%20Little%20Havana%20area.%20The%20neighboring%20businesses%20include%20a%20drive-through%20car%20wash%20and%20a%20strip%20mall%20featuring%20a%20massage%20parlour%20and%20a%20sandwich%20shop%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20address%20had%20been%20home%20to%20the%20IHOP%20for%20decades%2C%20%3Cem%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20IHOP%20employee%20told%20%3Cem%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20she%20had%20never%20heard%20of%20Morton%2C%20Camshaft%20Capital%20Fund%2C%20or%20Byju%E2%80%99s%2C%20indicating%20no%20business%20activity%20related%20to%20the%20hedge%20fund%20at%20that%20location.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fem%3E%20also%20noted%20that%20Camshaft%2C%20in%20an%20unrelated%20lawsuit%20filed%20by%20the%20hedge%20fund%2C%20said%20its%20principal%20place%20of%20business%20is%20in%20the%20Virgin%20Islands.%20This%20lawsuit%20was%20filed%20in%20June.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lenders%E2%80%99%20agent%2C%20Glas%20Trust%2C%20argued%20that%20Byju%E2%80%99s%20has%20worked%20hard%20to%20hide%20the%20%24533%20million%20owed%20to%20borrowers%2C%20intending%20to%20slow%20down%20and%20obstruct%20creditors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EByju%E2%80%99s%20has%20denied%20these%20allegations%2C%20reported%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businesstoday.in%2Fentrepreneurship%2Fstart-up%2Fstory%2Fbyjus-refutes-accusations-of-concealing-533-million-in-hedge-fund-cites-credit-agreement-compliance-398189-2023-09-13%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Today%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20a%20commercially%20prudent%20borrower%20and%20like%20any%20other%20large%20corporate%20treasury%2C%20Byju%E2%80%99s%20Alpha%20has%20made%20investments%20in%20a%20multi-hundred%20billion%20dollar%20fund%20with%20high%20security%20fixed%20income%20instruments.%20Our%20Credit%20Agreement%20with%20the%20lenders%20does%20not%20prohibit%20or%20restrict%20the%20movement%20or%20investment%20of%20monies%20disbursed%20thereunder.%20There%20is%20no%20requirement%20for%20Byju%E2%80%99s%20to%20maintain%20cash%20as%20collateral%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20Byju%E2%80%99s%20spokesperson%20told%20%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Today%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGlas%20Trust%2C%20the%20agent%20for%20the%20creditors%2C%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20informed%20Camshaft%20about%20the%20lawsuit%2C%20the%20fund%E2%80%99s%20lawyers%20told%20%3Cem%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fem%3E.%20%E2%80%9CCamshaft%20vigorously%20denies%20the%20statements%20made%20in%20Glas%20Trust%20Company%E2%80%99s%E2%80%9D%20court%20filing%2C%20Camshaft%20lawyer%20David%20Massey%20said%20in%20an%20emailed%20statement%2C%20noted%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20else%20have%20the%20lenders%20said%20in%20their%20court%20filings%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lenders%20argued%20that%20the%20%24533%20million%20transferred%20is%20collateral%20for%20a%20%241.2%20billion%20loan%2C%20and%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20dispute%20between%20Byju%E2%80%99s%20and%20the%20lenders%20regarding%20the%20loan%20status.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%20that%20Byju%E2%80%99s%20is%20attempting%20to%20negotiate%20a%20deal%20with%20creditors%20and%20proposing%20to%20buy%20back%20the%20loan%20within%20six%20months%2C%20through%20selling%20overseas%20assets%20to%20private%20equity%20and%20strategic%20investors.%20(A%20loan%20buy%20back%20occurs%20when%20a%20borrower%20repays%20a%20portion%20of%20the%20loan%20for%20less%20than%20the%20promised%20amount.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lenders%20also%20highlighted%20that%20Byju%E2%80%99s%20sent%20the%20money%20to%20Camshaft%2C%20which%20appears%20to%20cater%20to%20smaller%20clients%20and%20accepts%20investments%20as%20low%20as%20%2450%2C000%20for%20a%20hedge%20fund.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20missing%20cash%20is%20at%20the%20center%20of%20the%20lenders%E2%80%99%20actions%2C%20the%20report%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20lenders%20had%20gained%20control%20of%20the%20Byju%E2%80%99s%20unit%20that%20issued%20the%20debt%2C%20but%20the%20money%20had%20already%20disappeared.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20May%2C%20Byju%E2%80%99s%20Alpha%E2%80%99s%20lawyer%20had%20said%2C%20during%20a%20court%20hearing%2C%20that%20the%20company%20was%20trying%20to%20protect%20the%20money%20from%20predatory%20lenders.%20The%20company%20had%20a%20right%20to%20transfer%20the%20money%20under%20the%20loan%20agreement%2C%20the%20lawyer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EByju%E2%80%99s%20accused%20the%20lenders%20of%20seeking%20control%20of%20the%20entire%20ed-tech%20empire%20led%20by%20its%20founder%2C%20Byju%20Raveendran.%20It%20had%20asked%20a%20Delaware%20judge%20to%20reject%20the%20default%20declared%20by%20Glas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20startup%20was%20founded%20in%202015%2C%20Byju%E2%80%99s%20has%20received%20significant%20investments%20from%20major%20players%20in%20the%20tech%20industry%2C%20such%20as%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%E2%80%99s%20Chan%20Zuckerberg%20Initiative%2C%20Silver%20Lake%20Management%2C%20and%20Naspers%20Ltd.%20Last%20year%2C%20Byju%E2%80%99s%20was%20valued%20at%20over%20%2420%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lenders%E2%80%99%20lawsuit%20aims%20to%20trace%20the%20money%20and%20recover%20any%20excess%20management%20fees%20paid%20to%20Camshaft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20the%20time%20of%20the%20report%2C%20Camshaft%20had%20not%20yet%20filed%20a%20response%20to%20the%20lawsuit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBackstory%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20November%202021%2C%20the%20company%20had%20raised%20a%20%241.2%20billion%20term%20loan%20from%20a%20group%20of%20US-based%20creditors.%20However%2C%20in%20June%20this%20year%2C%20Byju%E2%80%99s%20missed%20a%20%2440%20million%20interest%20payment%20on%20this%20loan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlpha%20is%20the%20borrowing%20entity%20under%20the%20Term%20Loan%20B.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20term%20loan%20provides%20borrowers%20with%20a%20lump%20sum%20of%20cash%20upfront%20in%20exchange%20for%20specific%20borrowing%20terms.%20Borrowers%20agree%20to%20pay%20their%20lenders%20a%20fixed%20amount%20over%20a%20certain%20repayment%20schedule%20with%20either%20a%20fixed%20or%20floating%20interest%20rate.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20company%20missed%20the%20quarterly%20payment%20schedule%20on%20June%205%2C%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Ftech%2Ftechnology%2Fbyjus-files-suit-challenging-loan-acceleration-seeks-redwoods-disqualification%2Farticleshow%2F100781321.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Esued%3C%2Fa%3E%20its%20lenders%20and%20related%20entities%20for%20accelerating%20the%20repayment%20of%20the%20term%20loan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EByju%E2%80%99s%20declared%20that%20it%20would%20withhold%20any%20further%20payments%2C%20including%20interest%2C%20to%20the%20lenders%20until%20the%20court%20settles%20the%20dispute.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20a%20matter%20of%20fact%2C%20the%20Delaware%20court%20ruling%20in%20June%20this%20year%20rejected%20the%20lenders%E2%80%99%20application%20for%20information%20in%20relation%20to%20the%20amount%20in%20question%20i.e.%20part%20of%20the%20funds%20received%20by%20BYJU%E2%80%99S%20Alpha%2C%20the%20borrowing%20entity%20under%20the%20TLB%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Today%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%2C%20citing%20the%20company%E2%80%99s%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694596686000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Fbyjus-transferred-533-million-to-a-hedge-fund-that-houses-us-pancake-shop-report%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20Bloomberg%20report%20has%20said%20that%20while%20lenders%20argued%20that%20the%20amount%20transferred%20is%20collateral%20for%20a%20%241.2%20billion%20loan%2C%20there's%20a%20dispute%20between%20the%20e-learning%20behemoth%20and%20lenders%20over%20the%20loan%20status.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Fbyjus-transferred-533-million-to-a-hedge-fund-that-houses-us-pancake-shop-report%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22At%20least%2030%2C000%20displaced%20after%20Libya%20floods%20-%20with%20fatalities%20expected%20to%20rise%20significantly%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694595540000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F09%2F1600x900%2Fskynews-libya-derna-flood_6283127.jpg%3F20230913094719%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Flibya-floods-at-least-30000-displaced-with-fatalities-expected-to-rise-significantly-12960377%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22At%20least%2030%2C000%20people%20have%20been%20displaced%20in%20the%20town%20hardest%20hit%20by%20floods%20in%20Libya.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A276%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Flibya-floods-at-least-30-000-displaced-with-fatalities-expected-to-rise-significantly-12960377%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Flibya-floods-at-least-30-000-displaced-with-fatalities-expected-to-rise-significantly-12960377%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Flibya-floods-at-least-30-000-displaced-with-fatalities-expected-to-rise-significantly-12960377%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Coffee%20Day%20Global%20settles%20with%20creditor%3B%20NCLAT%20sets%20aside%20insolvency%20order%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694595301000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2019-11%2F08%2Ffull%2F1573231431-1068.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fcoffee-day-global-settles-with-creditor-nclat-sets-aside-insolvency-order-123091300522_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22On%20July%2020%2C%20the%20Bengaluru%20bench%20of%20NCLT%20had%20directed%20the%20initiation%20of%20insolvency%20proceedings%20against%20CDGL%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fcoffee-day-global-settles-with-creditor-nclat-sets-aside-insolvency-order-123091300522_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22With%20Delhi%20Atop%20List%20of%20PM2.5%20Exposed%20Cities%2C%20Nitrogen%20Oxide%20Emissions%20Also%20Rise%20in%20South%20Asia%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F11%2F01140646%2F2019_10img31_Oct_2019_PTI10_31_2019_000257B.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20South%20Asia%20has%20some%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20only%20areas%20where%20nitrogen%20dioxide%20(NO%3Csub%3E2%3C%2Fsub%3E)%20levels%20are%20increasing%2C%20an%20analysis%20by%20State%20of%20Global%20Air%20(SOGA)%20has%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESOGA%20is%20a%20research%20and%20outreach%20initiative%20that%20aims%20to%20provide%20meaningful%20information%20about%20air%20quality%20in%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20published%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.stateofglobalair.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fdocuments%2F2023-09%2Fsoga_reg._aq_snapshot_9-11-23_final.pdf%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98snapshot%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20air%20quality%20in%20the%20South%20Asia%20region%20on%20Tuesday%20(September%2012)%20that%20draws%20from%20a%20global%20air%20quality%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.stateofglobalair.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fdocuments%2F2022-08%2F2022-soga-cities-report.pdf%5C%22%3Eanalysis%3C%2Fa%3E%20it%20concluded%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20snapshot%20finds%20that%20while%20levels%20of%20NO%3Csub%3E2%3C%2Fsub%3E%20%E2%80%93%20a%20pollutant%20belonging%20to%20the%20highly%20reactive%20nitrogen%20oxides%20(NO%3Csub%3Ex%3C%2Fsub%3E)%20group%20of%20gases%20%E2%80%93%20have%20declined%20in%20North%20America%2C%20Western%20Europe%20and%20China%20over%20recent%20years%2C%20they%20have%20been%20increasing%20in%20South%20Asia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20%E2%80%9Cfuelled%20by%20large-scale%20programs%20to%20expand%20access%20to%20energy%20to%20households%2C%20expanding%20industries%20and%20increases%20in%20vehicle%20ownership%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20India%2C%20major%20sources%20of%20NO%3Csub%3E2%3C%2Fsub%3E%20are%20coal-based%20energy%20production%2C%20industrial%20processes%20and%20on-road%20transportation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExposure%20to%20the%20gas%20can%20irritate%20the%20airways%2C%20aggravate%20existing%20respiratory%20diseases%20and%20increase%20the%20susceptibility%20to%20new%20ones%2C%20and%20heighten%20the%20risk%20of%20asthma%20development%20in%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20data%20from%202019%2C%20Bengaluru%20and%20Hyderabad%20top%20the%20list%20of%20major%20South%20Asian%20cities%20in%20terms%20of%20population-weighted%20NO%3Csub%3E2%3C%2Fsub%3E%20exposure%2C%20SOGA%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2F31191817%2F2022_10img31_Oct_2022_PTI10_31_2022_000190B-1024x691.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2F31191817%2F2022_10img31_Oct_2022_PTI10_31_2022_000190B-1024x691.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2F31191817%2F2022_10img31_Oct_2022_PTI10_31_2022_000190B-300x203.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F10%2F31191817%2F2022_10img31_Oct_2022_PTI10_31_2022_000190B.jpg%201200w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-626666%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22567%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ENO%3Csub%3E2%3C%2Fsub%3E%20is%20also%20a%20key%20marker%20for%20traffic-related%20air%20pollution%2C%20the%20snapshot%20said.%20Photo%3A%20PTI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20added%20that%20although%20South%20Asia%20stands%20out%20for%20the%20increase%20in%20its%20NO%3Csub%3Ex%3C%2Fsub%3E%20emissions%2C%20NO%3Csub%3E2%3C%2Fsub%3E%20emissions%20are%20low%20here%20compared%20to%20other%20regions%20in%20the%20world%2C%20and%20some%20countries%20in%20South%20Asia%20have%20NO%3Csub%3E2%3C%2Fsub%3E%20quality%20standards%20in%20line%20with%20interim%20targets%20recommended%20by%20the%20WHO.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20cited%20a%20policy%20action%20from%20India%2C%20namely%20the%20Union%20government%20moving%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2Fnewsite%2Fprintrelease.aspx%3Frelid%3D134232%5C%22%3Edirectly%20from%20the%20BS-IV%20emission%20norms%20to%20BS-VI%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20an%20example%20of%20an%20initiative%20that%20will%20significantly%20reduce%20NO%3Csub%3Ex%3C%2Fsub%3E%20emissions%20and%20bring%20%E2%80%9Cclean%20air%20dividends%20in%20the%20next%20decade%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20India%2C%20addressing%20source-specific%20emissions%20(for%20example%2C%20transportation)%20have%20begun%20to%20show%20dividends.%20In%20fact%2C%20satellite-based%20estimates%20indicate%20that%20NO%3Csub%3E2%3C%2Fsub%3E%20levels%20may%20be%20beginning%20to%20decline%20in%20some%20Indian%20cities%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20snapshot%20also%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20another%20major%20air%20pollutant%2C%20PM%3Csub%3E2.5%3C%2Fsub%3E%2C%20SOGA%20noted%20that%20exposure%20it%20to%20remains%20high%20in%20South%20Asian%20cities.%20Less%20than%201%25%20of%20these%20cities%20meet%20the%20WHO%E2%80%99s%20PM%3Csub%3E2.5%3C%2Fsub%3E%20guidelines%2C%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20list%20it%20provided%20of%20major%20South%20Asian%20cities%20with%20the%20most%20population-weighted%20PM%3Csub%3E2.5%3C%2Fsub%3E%20exposure%20as%20of%202019%20had%20Delhi%20and%20Kolkata%20in%20the%20first%20and%20second%20positions%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20same%20two%20cities%20topped%20the%20SOGA%E2%80%99s%20list%20for%20major%20cities%20across%20the%20world.%20Beijing%20came%20in%20at%20a%20farther%20ninth%20and%20Mumbai%20clocked%20in%20at%2014th.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPM%3Csub%3E2.5%3C%2Fsub%3E%20is%20any%20particulate%20matter%20that%20has%20a%20maximum%20width%20of%202.5%20micrometres%20(0.0025%20mm).%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fairquality.gsfc.nasa.gov%2Fparticulate-matter%5C%22%3Emajority%20of%20air%20pollution%20deaths%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20associated%20with%20PM%3Csub%3E2.5%3C%2Fsub%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESOGA%E2%80%99s%20snapshot%20said%20that%2034%25%20of%20deaths%20in%20South%20Asia%E2%80%99s%2020%20most%20populated%20cities%20are%20linked%20to%20exposure%20to%20PM%3Csub%3E2.5%3C%2Fsub%3E%2C%20and%20that%20Indians%20lose%201.5%20years%20of%20their%20lives%20to%20PM%3Csub%3E2.5%3C%2Fsub%3E%20pollution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20study%20by%20the%20University%20of%20Chicago%20Energy%20Policy%20Institute%20last%20month%20said%20that%20particulate%20pollution%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22file%3A%2FC%3A%2FUsers%2Fairsu%2FDownloads%2FIndia-FactSheet-2023_Final.pdf%5C%22%3Etakes%205.3%20years%20off%20the%20lifespan%20of%20an%20average%20Indian%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20that%20if%20India%20were%20to%20reduce%20particulate%20pollution%20to%20meet%20the%20WHO%20guideline%2C%20Delhiites%20stand%20to%20gain%20close%20to%2012%20years%20in%20life%20expectancy.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694593535000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%